Apotoforma hodgesi is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found in Panama.
The wingspan is about 14 mm. The ground colour of the forewings is brownish with an cinnamon hue and with an indistinct brownish grey spot at the middle of the costa followed by a trace of suffusion marked by a few black scales. There is also a row of delicate brownish terminal dots. The hindwings are brown-grey.